title: Vilseck keeps playoff hopes alive at Kaiserslautern's expense
text:
Vilseck keeps playoff hopes alive at Kaiserslautern's expense Vilseck page 
VILSECK, Germany -- The Vilseck Falcons earned their second straight victory Saturday with a 14-0 defeat of the visiting Kaiserslautern Raiders. 
Vilseck improves to 2-2 with the victory, its second in a row after last weekend's 14-10 upset of Wiesbaden. The Falcons take on defending champion Ramstein - whom they tied in a regular-season opener that didn't count towards playoff seeding - in their regular-season finale next weekend. 
Kaiserslautern, meanwhile, is the first team out of playoff contention in the six-team Division I field. The 0-4 Raiders face Lakenheath next weekend. 
Drew Pinckney scored on a 5-yard run in the first half and Austin Archangel threw a 32-yard touchdown pass to Bryce McGregor in the second half. 
Aamaree Harrington led the Falcons with 126 rushing yards on 19 carries. Pinckney also paced the Falcon defense with 14 tackles, while Derek Davis made 10. 
Jamarkus Myles carried 28 times for 102 yards for Kaiserslautern Join the conversation and share your voice.
